    <h2>Understanding Our Refund Process</h2>

    <div class="section-title">⟡ When Can a Refund Be Requested?</div>
    <p>
        Refunds can be requested whenever an order was not completed successfully, cancelled,
        or if the user made a mistake while creating an order.  
        Refund eligibility depends on verification of the order details and confirmation from both sides.
    </p>

    <div class="section-title">⟡ How Long Does a Refund Take?</div>
    <p>
        Refund review is normally processed within **1–24 hours**, depending on the situation.
        Additional information may be requested to confirm details for security purposes.
    </p>

    <div class="section-title">⟡ What Information Is Needed?</div>
    <p>
        To request a refund, users may be asked to provide:
        <br>• The order reference  
        <br>• The reason for requesting refund  
        <br>• Any supporting details for verification  
    </p>

    <div class="section-title">⟡ Important Notes</div>
    <p>
        • Refunds can only be sent back to the original sender.  
        <br>• Processing time may vary depending on review workload.  
        <br>• False or incomplete information may delay processing.  
    </p>

